      "question": "Should tests cover TypeScript type narrowing behavior (i.e., verify that isMarketListStatusFilter and isMarketListSort act as proper type guards), or just boolean return values?",
      "category": "requirements",
      "why_it_matters": "Type guard tests would need different assertions than simple boolean checks, and may require TypeScript-specific test patterns."
    },
    {
      "id": "q2",
      "question": "Should edge cases like null, undefined, empty string, and whitespace-only strings be tested for each function, or just the happy-path valid/invalid values?",
      "category": "requirements",
      "why_it_matters": "The code handles null in type guards and whitespace in normalizeMarketListFilters — edge case coverage determines test thoroughness."
    },
    {
      "id": "q3",
      "question": "For readMarketListFiltersFromSearchParams, should we test round-trip consistency (marketListSearchParams -> readMarketListFiltersFromSearchParams)?",
      "category": "design",
      "why_it_matters": "Round-trip tests verify the encode/decode pair works together, catching subtle serialization mismatches that unit tests of each function alone might miss."
    }
  ],
  "assumptions": [
    {
      "id": "a1",
      "assumption": "Tests should use vitest with `describe`/`it`/`expect` imports, matching the format.test.ts pattern, placed at frontend/src/__tests__/marketListFilters.test.ts",
